                                    Vehicle manufacturers must document their determination that the infrastructure is not in place for each country to which they plan to export vehicles and must retain the documentation in their files for at least five years after date of its creation for the purpose of demonstrating compliance.

Documentation is to include descriptions of:

â¢ Products in which the substitute is needed;

â¢ Substitutes examined and rejected for the destination country;

â¢ Reason for rejection of other alternatives; and

â¢ Anticipated date other substitutes will be available and projected date of transition in the destination country.

Users are required to document and retain the results of their technical investigation of alternatives for the purpose of demonstrating compliance. Information should include descriptions of:
â¢ Process or product in which the substitute is needed;
â¢ Substitutes examined and rejected;
â¢ Reason for rejection of other alternatives, e.g., performance, technical or safety standards; and/or
â¢ Anticipated date other substitutes will be available and projected time for switching.

